VICE President Samia Suluhu has said the fifth phase government increased health budget from 30bn/- to 270bn/- purposely to improve people’s heath. Addressing residents in Nkasi District, Rukwa on Friday evening, Ms Samia said due to the increased budget in the key sector like health, there is no scarcity of medicines and other important services in public health facilities. She promised that CCM’s government will continue to improve the sector by constructing more 98 hospitals in district councils with no health centers. Ms Samia, who was asking residents in Nkasi to vote for CCM Presidential candidate Dr John Magufuli, promised that the ruling party will ensure every Tanzanian gets health insurance if given another opportunity to form the government.